title: Romanticism - the Culture of XIX century (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
G. Braziller | 1965 | Pdf | Eng | 351 pages | 49.1 MB

Romanticism began at a period in the late eighteenth century when a small, embattled and alienated group of cultural leaders throughout Europe almost simultaneously began to feel that they had arrived at a way of viewing the world which was profoundly different from any worldview that ever appeared before.
This forced them to see everything in an entirely new perspective philosophy, religion, arts, history, politics, cience. Often misunderstood  even by their admirers, and for the most part still today, these men gave birth to a movement in which is best found the key to the dynamic of the nineteenth century
